[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T21:10:55+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"boeing cst100 starliner\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QxaiXsnYzvb3h72qTpwg7mHVQBY=/100x0:1180x720/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507799/cst100_hero_lrg_1280x720.0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Boeing</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8ER12h\">During a <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/clip/Ugkxbm1svf7LFDYt9UxO-kU4ZqwfMAa7AfiN\">press conference</a> today, NASA representatives confirmed they have a contingency plan to bring astronauts Barry Wilmore and Sunita Williams home from the International Space Station (ISS) early next year.  If they\u2019re unable to leave sooner aboard the Boeing Starliner spacecraft that brought them there, the backup plan would rely on SpaceX\u2019s Crew-9 mission, which has had its launch delayed while officials figure out what to do next.</p>\n<p id=\"bKv3W2\">After a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/5/24172080/boeing-starliner-crewed-flight-test-launch-success\">successful crewed launch of the Boein", "id": 993983, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215584/boeing-starliner-astronauts-iss-spacex-nasa", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Boeing Starliner astronauts might get a ride home from SpaceX \u2014 in 2025", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T20:49:07+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of the Selfie Control filter on Instagram\u2019s camera screen.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7oJMnOHGsXbTcYrZCpm6jDNz2aQ=/0x98:1686x1222/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507736/selfilecontrol.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Visit Jackson Hole</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"7LUivd\">Wyoming\u2019s Jackson Hole Travel &amp; Tourism Board has created <a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20240730703148/en/Visit-Jackson-Hole-Launches-Instagram-Filter-to-Make-Visitors-Aware-of-Safe-Distances-for-Wildlife-Photos\">an open-source Instagram filter</a> to help visitors gauge if they\u2019re at a safe distance from wildlife to take photos. The board hopes the tool will help better protect tourists visiting wildlife destinations \u2014 and the animals they\u2019re watching \u2014 during the busy summer travel season.</p>\n<p id=\"kB24Vv\">To use the filter, visitors to the valley and wilderness recreation area need to open up the <a href=\"https:", "id": 993578, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215490/jackson-hole-travel-tourism-board-instagram-filter-animals-national-park-safety", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Jackson Hole\u2019s new Instagram filter warns you when you\u2019re dangerously close to wildlife", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T20:33:14+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Sonos Ace wireless headphones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_nJu7G1HGSRK_uZ985RLRaK1k-o=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507706/DSCF7347_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vUDmIx\">Sonos CEO Patrick Spence said the new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24169086/sonos-ace-headphones-review\">Ace headphones</a> helped spur \u201cyear over year revenue growth\u201d that slightly exceeded the company\u2019s expectations as part of its <a href=\"https://investors.sonos.com/news-and-events/investor-news/latest-news/2024/Sonos-Reports-Third-Quarter-Fiscal-2024-Results/\">third quarter earnings</a> on Wednesday afternoon. But he quickly moved on to address the company\u2019s ongoing app woes, which will soon have a negative impact on Sonos\u2019 bottom line.</p>\n<p id=\"tcESII\">\u201cThis was overshadowed by the problems that our customers and partners experienced as ", "id": 993579, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215589/sonos-q3-2024-earnings-ace-headphone-buggy-app", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sonos CEO says headphone launch was \u2018overshadowed\u2019 by app controversy", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T20:25:03+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Reddit wordmark on a yellow background, with its Snoo character framing it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ToNYMikweGsoGUnwdv3ladAwaDk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507674/STK115_Reddit_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0rUuwO\">You might have to pay to access some subreddits in the future. During an earnings call on Tuesday, Reddit CEO Steve Huffman hinted at \u201cnew types of subreddits that can be built that may have exclusive content or private areas.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"K5liJG\">\u201cI think the existing, altruistic, free version of Reddit will continue to exist and grow and thrive just the way it has,\u201d Huffman said. \u201cBut now we will unlock the door for new use cases, new types of subreddits that can be built.\u201d Huffman said he doesn\u2019t think these gated communities would \u201ccannibalize\u201d the site, which has seen an increase in users over the past few months. The site\u2019s", "id": 993580, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215505/reddit-paid-subreddits-steve-huffman-q2-2024-earnings", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Reddit might let users make paid subreddits", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T19:44:28+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Tim Walz in a suit, wearing a camo-printed hat that says HARRIS WALZ in bright orange letters.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cnQYH2NLSgSRotWXjJR0RNLzTQg=/13x0:1915x1268/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507557/Screenshot_2024_08_07_at_11.03.53_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Tim Walz</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"exKKyx\">Vice President Kamala Harris\u2019 <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24210484/kamala-harris-vp-tim-walz-running-mate-minnesota\">pick for running mate</a> is Minnesota Governor Tim Walz, a former teacher and football coach whose straightforward manner of speaking has endeared him to many and helped launch his name into the public consciousness.</p>\n<p id=\"6RTMQf\">Walz\u2019s public persona has what many would describe as \u201cdad energy.\u201d He makes unsubtle jokes and regularly <a href=\"https://x.com/GovTimWalz/status/1817558482725298208\">posts pictures of his dogs</a>. During <a href=\"https://x.com/metzgov/s", "id": 993192, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215327/kamala-harris-tim-walz-memes-chappell-roan-midwest-princess-camo-hat", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Kamala Harris is Brat, Tim Walz is Midwest Princess", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T19:39:49+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A computer chip, covered in a silver heatspreader with identifying text, atop a blue Intel box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bBsTjsacwwMbKSw6a0t9fizrDUA=/0x0:1200x800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507539/intel_13900k_tomwarren__2_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>An Intel Core i9-13900K CPU, one of the first types identified to sometimes crash this way.</em> | Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"D6aau6\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206529/intel-13th-14th-gen-crashing-instability-cpu-voltage-q-a\">There is no fix</a> for Intel\u2019s crashing 13th and 14th Gen Raptor Lake desktop processors. If your chip isn\u2019t yet damaged, please apply motherboard BIOS updates early and often to prevent issues. If it\u2019s already damaged, your only option is to exchange it. </p>\n<p id=\"1Pukee\">But what if you didn\u2019t buy a <em>chip \u2014 </em>but, rather, an entire PC? Will PC makers have your back? Will they", "id": 993193, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215440/intel-13th-14th-gen-crash-raptor-lake-integrator-warranty-lenovo-dell-hp-acer-asus", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Will PC makers replace your crashing Intel chip? We asked 14 of them", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T19:03:49+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Art depicting characters from Fortnite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MqS1M30Yr5QRuPozX75qhkbqDn8=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507495/C5S3_Battle_Pass_Lineup_EN.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Characters from the Chapter 5: Season 3 battle pass.</em> | Image: Epic Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OML67Y\">Epic Games is making a major change to <em>Fortnite</em>\u2019s<em> </em>battle passes that should remove some angst if you can\u2019t buy or complete a pass before the end of a season.</p>\n<p id=\"zyT6v5\"><em>Fortnite</em>\u2019s battle passes offer a bunch of exclusive in-game rewards that you can only obtain during an individual season, but that means you might miss out on rewards entirely if you can\u2019t level up enough or don\u2019t buy the pass before it expires. To help alleviate that pressure, Epic <a href=\"https://www.fortnite.com/news/change-to-item-exclusivity-in-future-fortnite-battle-passes\">announced on Wedne", "id": 993194, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215375/fortnite-battle-pass-rewards-back-around-item-shop", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Fortnite will bring battle pass rewards back around", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T19:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Home office with corner desk, green highlights, and a windows with blinds down.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gVkiOppNIq0n1_GmltgKV76mrBY=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507479/247212_WOYD_JW_JWeatherbed_0009.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>A magically green room full of gaming mementos.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24212190/work-home-desk-cthulhu-msi-logitech\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 993195, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24212190/work-home-desk-cthulhu-msi-logitech", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What\u2019s on your desk, Jess Weatherbed?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T18:48:53+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/WEGxR4lTB68BLwMUxEKKAKIvJ_U=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507454/STK206_Tim_Walz_Kristen_Radtke_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XyQBZt\">Last year, when Minnesota\u2019s progressive politicians coalesced around a bill to raise the minimum pay for Uber and Lyft drivers in the state, their ostensibly left-of-center governor surprised them all by pulling a move he had yet to use while in office: <a href=\"https://www.house.mn.gov/NewLaws/story/2023/5502#:~:text=He%20echoed%20arguments%20made%20during,rates%20will%20limit%2C%20and%20potentially\">he vetoed it</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"ZSMCSs\">Uber and Lyft were <a href=\"https://www.minnpost.com/state-government/2024/05/two-paths-a-look-at-uber-and-lyfts-threat-to-leave-minnesota/\">threatening to stop operating in Minnesota</a> if the bill was signed into law, and Governor Tim Walz was ", "id": 992811, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24214575/tim-walz-uber-lyft-driver-pay-veto-vp-minnesota", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Uber\u00a0and\u00a0Lyft\u00a0threatened to leave Minnesota \u2014 then Tim Walz stepped in", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T17:38:53+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A hands-on photo of the Google TV Streamer set-top box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5ZoGHITFy8ZTNpQaXjQqtyGPp28=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507360/DSCF0055.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cjtePD\">The Chromecast <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214471/google-chromecast-line-discontinued\">is going away</a> after more than a decade in Google\u2019s hardware portfolio, with the company phasing it out to make room for <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214055/google-tv-streamer-features-price-matter-thread\">the new Google TV Streamer</a>. In 2013, the timing was perfect for the Chromecast\u2019s success. Most TVs of that era had rudimentary entertainment apps that were often slow, so beaming content from your phone to a TV made a lot of sense.</p>\n<p id=\"qsOPi6\">But times have changed. With the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21495609/google-chromecast-2020-review-streaming-remote-control\">Chromecas", "id": 992393, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215275/google-tv-streamer-chromecast-gemini-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Why Google decided now\u2019s the time to move on from Chromecast", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T17:24:07+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A view of white corals with a few small fish swimming around them.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LKj6p7NR9eQ9YaU9-BepVWC3cLY=/316x0:3684x2245/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507332/image_9.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Bleached coral in the Great Barrier Reef in 2024.</em> | Photo: Ove Hoegh-Guldberg</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jV9J7X\">The Great Barrier Reef and surrounding waters have reached hotter temperatures over the past decade than they have in at least 400 years because of climate change, according to new research <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-024-07672-x\">published in the journal <em>Nature</em></a>. </p>\n<p id=\"iQdoVt\">It\u2019s a stark warning. The survival of the Great Barrier Reef is essentially now in human hands. Corals around the world face <a href=\"https://climate.nasa.gov/explore/ask-nasa-climate/3290/vanishing-corals-part-two-climate-change-is-stressing-corals-but-theres-hope/\">near ex", "id": 992394, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215219/great-barrier-reef-record-temperatures-coral-research", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Great Barrier Reef faces its biggest threat in centuries", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T17:12:21+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y5jIMu_VkfcjqfUxoOhbm_MqVVU=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507313/247075_Humane_AI_pin_AKrales_0056.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"mjNOlO\">Shortly after Humane released its $699 AI Pin in April, the returns started flowing in.</p>\n<p id=\"VvN9xV\">Between May and August, more AI Pins were returned than purchased, according to internal sales data obtained by <em>The Verge</em>. By June, only around 8,000 units <em>hadn\u2019t</em> been returned, a source with direct knowledge of sales and return data told me. As of today, the number of units still in customer hands had fallen closer to 7,000, a source with direct knowledge said. </p>\n<p id=\"lQ1Ait\">At launch, the AI Pin was met with overwhelmingly negative reviews. Our own David Pierce said it \u201c<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24126502/humane-ai-pin-review\">just ", "id": 992395, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24211339/humane-ai-pin-more-daily-returns-than-sales", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Humane\u2019s daily returns are outpacing sales", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T17:03:31+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Instagram logo with geometric design background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sd2INztbmR6Cb2UQrNgszGw8stY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507287/acastro_STK070__03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fiK2dq\">Instagram is making \u201cviews\u201d the primary metric across all of its formats, meaning that creators will be able to track the same metric across Reels, Stories, photos, and more. The change will roll out in the coming weeks, according to a post on <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/C-X-fRPRl10/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&amp;igsh=OXBuODVybnlzazlj&amp;img_index=2\">Instagram\u2019s creators account</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><div id=\"wZ5QSV\">\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\"><div style=\"padding: 16px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/reel/C-X7FtePYyj/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\"line-height: 0; pad", "id": 992396, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215398/instagram-primary-metric-views", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Instagram is making views the primary metric for content", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T16:55:48+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D-MA)\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IA4wWN6mkSDnB50KPkoe6G2tOyU=/0x0:4941x3294/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507271/2160975539.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ua3Uot\">A new joint venture between three streaming leaders could create a monopoly problem in sports television, three lawmakers warn US regulators <a href=\"https://www.warren.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/warren_castro_letter_to_doj_and_fcc_re_sports_streaming_jv.pdf\">in a letter</a> <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5685739/2024/08/07/dept-of-justice-disney-fox-warner-bros-tnt/?redirected=1\">first reported by <em>The Athletic</em></a>.</p>\n<p id=\"IwMJOk\">Sens. Elizabeth Warren (D-MA), Bernie Sanders (I-VT), and Rep. Joaquin Castro (D-TX) are asking<strong> </strong>law enforcers to investigate the joint venture between Disney, Fox, and Warner Bros. to create a new service, Venu Sports. The streaming service is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.co", "id": 992397, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215343/warren-sanders-castro-doj-joint-sports-venture-disney-fox-warner-bros", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Senators want an investigation of the Fox\u2013Disney\u2013Warner Bros sports bundle", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A laughing skull made out of code.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2p4CRjOXoQ-szKe69X0zWyg2fVM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507130/246992_AI_at_Work_OBITS_ECarter.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Erik Carter</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"buqFTv\">Thousands of families have witnessed <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24065145/ai-obituary-spam-generative-clickbait\">fake obituaries of loved ones crowd Google search results</a>. As <em>The Verge</em> reported in February, the obituaries \u2014 which often appear to be AI-generated \u2014 target everyday people, not just celebrities, and are written to extract clicks and subsequent ad revenue from readers.</p>\n<p id=\"0tS85j\"><a href=\"https://checkmyads.org/fake-obituary-advertising-spam/\">A new report by watchdog organization Check My Ads</a> traced some of the middlemen profiting from obituary spam: ad exchanges, or the companies that connect brands that want ", "id": 991873, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24213699/obituray-spam-ai-advertising-ad-exchanges-google-search", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The ad companies making money off of obituary spam", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T15:48:18+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KuMsFzFHYIx5NAwOkJKifkVTN9c=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507104/370bce44dde6727b566a5bc1821a947521a2fbe7.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: LocalThunk</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"77gZz8\"><em>Balatro</em>, the delightful poker roguelike that\u2019s one of my favorite video games of this year, will be getting a free \u201cmajor gameplay update\u201d in 2025, <a href=\"https://x.com/BalatroGame/status/1821184855876804841\">according to developer LocalThunk</a>. The update will \u201cbring new ideas and strategies to the game\u201d and will be released for all platforms (it\u2019s available on Steam, PlayStation, Nintendo Switch, and Xbox), LocalThunk says.</p>\n<p id=\"M4c0hK\"><em>Balatro</em> launched <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24082252/balatro-review-poker-roguelike-videogame\">earlier this year</a>, and it\u2019s since become a smash hit thanks to its compelling gameplay loop that will have you saying ", "id": 991874, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215342/balatro-free-major-gameplay-update-2025", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Balatro is getting a free \u2018major gameplay update\u2019 in 2025", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T15:34:06+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The new 100W Anker Prime Charger floating against a rendered background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yd79nEj3IesR_MF_ypVVlDWQOyI=/0x1:866x578/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507091/anker_gan_charger1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Anker included thicker prongs and an improved center of gravity on its new 100W wall charger.</em> | Image: Anker</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"EnHteP\">The most notable upgrade on <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anker.com%2Fproducts%2Fa2688-anker-prime-charger-100w-3-ports-gan%3Fvariant%3D43931966079126&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F8%2F7%2F24215215%2Fanker-prime-charger-usb-c-gan-power\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Anker\u2019s new Prime Charger</a> isn\u2019t how much power it can deliver: it\u2019s the redesigned folding plug that now has thicker prongs with a \u201cfrosted finish\u201d that ", "id": 991458, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215215/anker-prime-charger-usb-c-gan-power", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Anker redesigned its wall charger so it won\u2019t constantly fall out of the outlet", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T15:20:50+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Close-up of the Fitbit Ace LTE in the Spicy Pebble variant with a neon green bumper.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/b-soeCSOMwHEcEhRuUp11QV-n0A=/0x0:6589x4393/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507065/247127_Fitbit_Ace_LTE_VSong_0007.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Fitbit\u2019s rolling out Tap to Pay in time for the new school year.</em> | Photo by Victoria Song / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yXcwEV\">It\u2019s officially back-to-school season, so Fitbit\u2019s <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/fitbit/fitbit-ace-back-to-school-update/\">updating its kids-focused Ace LTE smartwatch</a> with some helpful features for parents and children. Namely, it\u2019s adding a Tap to Pay feature, launching two new games, and later this year, will allow users to add siblings as contacts in the Fitbit Ace app.</p>\n<p id=\"D78wGj\">Tap to Pay was mentioned as \u201ccoming soon\u201d when the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/29/24166168/fitbit-ace-lte-k", "id": 991459, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215312/fitbit-ace-lte-updates-kids-smartwatch-wearables", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The\u00a0Fitbit\u00a0Ace LTE\u00a0smartwatch\u00a0now lets kids buy stuff", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T15:19:36+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An Elgato Stream Deck Neo plugged into and sitting beside a laptop on a desk.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TO3GBqQwCVIIlNQLPP55NytSzsA=/0x2:8009x5341/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507058/Stream_Deck_Neo_Lifestyle_Shot_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Elgato\u2019s Stream Deck Neo is designed to be accessible to everybody, not just streamers.</em> | Image: Elgato</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gWeMJJ\">Here at <em>The Verge</em>, we\u2019re <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23700541/stream-deck-hacks-uses\">big Stream Deck fans</a>. However, Elgato\u2019s programmable macro controllers can be pricey, with the <a href=\"https://howl.me/cmPnc6psILW\">Stream Deck XL</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23517751/elgato-stream-deck-plus-review\">Deck Plus</a> retailing for <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Elgato-Stream-Deck-XL-customizable/dp/B07RL8H55Z/?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">$249.99</a> and <", "id": 991460, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214484/elgato-stream-deck-neo-apple-ipad-mini-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Elgato\u2019s desk-friendly Stream Deck Neo is matching its lowest price to date", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Rad Power Bikes RadKick\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AJtz8vprz0L4p04_WIDhW-O3uMk=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506849/547376_Footagepull.00_04_54_01.Still012_035726_original_1721944722.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Rad Power Bikes</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"d7VR94\">Rad Power Bikes announced a new more affordable, lighter-weight e-bike for urban commuters who just want a cheap, simple way to get around. Dubbed the RadKick, the new bike starts at $1,199, making it the Seattle-based company\u2019s most affordable model yet. </p>\n<p id=\"nFT4CJ\">And for those desiring fewer grease stains on their pant cuffs, the RadKick also comes with an optional belt drive in place of a traditional bike chain, which is a first for the company. </p>\n<p id=\"XvAdUY\">The low-step frame, integrated battery pack, and space for a plethora of front- and rear-rack optional add-ons could make this the ideal entry-level bike for ", "id": 990948, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215204/rad-power-bikes-radkick-ebike-affordable-belt-drive", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The RadKick is Rad Power Bikes\u2019 most affordable e-bike yet \u2014 and its first belt drive", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T13:19:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Disney logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SZnRQB2QMxXGqEiaJByWfSj-Thw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506762/STK080_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_9_disney_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"BIIBVS\">Disney Plus will soon no longer let you share your password with people outside your household. During an earnings call on Wednesday, Disney CEO Bob Iger said the crackdown will kick off \u201cin earnest\u201d this September.</p>\n<p id=\"6TkcIV\">The timeline for Disney\u2019s password-sharing crackdown has been a bit confusing so far. In February, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/7/24065158/disney-plus-password-account-sharing-summer-2024\">Disney announced plans to roll out paid sharing</a> and also began notifying users about the change. It then launched <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/4/24121189/disney-plus-paid-password-sharing-crackdown-june\">paid sharing", "id": 990498, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215224/disney-password-sharing-crackdown-september", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Disney\u2019s password-sharing crackdown starts \u2018in earnest\u2019 this September", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the OnePlus Open Apex Edition in crimson red.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JAehGwhYMfPHCGIWQE3xAGeyH4w=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506675/DSCF0127.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The crimson red \u2018Apex Edition\u2019 OnePlus Open is a stunner, and the color isn\u2019t the only thing that\u2019s different about it.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214775/oneplus-open-apex-edition-special-color\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 990499, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214775/oneplus-open-apex-edition-special-color", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "OnePlus tries to steal Google\u2019s thunder with a limited edition OnePlus Open", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T12:16:37+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The TCL NXTFrame TV displayed on a wall.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7O_IkIqvf1e7D1b7m47uKA6i3-c=/107x0:1333x817/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506606/A300W_landingpageHDR_Ultra_1440x817.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: TCL</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SccYgD\">It\u2019s been several years since Samsung first launched its popular Frame TV lineup, and now we\u2019re starting to see more brands release their own canvas-like designs. The latest is TCL\u2019s <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tcl.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fpress-releases%2Ftcl-nxtframe-tv&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F8%2F7%2F24215184%2Ftcl-nxtframe-samsung-frame-tv-knockoff-price-announcement\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">newly announced 4K QLED NXTFrame TV</a>, which has many of the features you\u2019d expect from an \u201cArt TV\u201d \u2014 including a magnetic wooden frame, ", "id": 990142, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215184/tcl-nxtframe-samsung-frame-tv-knockoff-price-announcement", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung\u2019s Frame TV is finally getting the knockoffs it deserves", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of car media logos in the rearview mirror of a car with fuzzy dice with the YouTube logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MIbfbz3Bni4mPcpQtSa5NmP5sYY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506534/247210_Car_Media_Quitting_CVirginia_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>From Car Throttle to Donut, countless YouTube creators are fleeing. But is this a new trend or a tale as old as venture capital? </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214600/car-youtube-quit-donut-car-throttle-hoonigan\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 990143, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214600/car-youtube-quit-donut-car-throttle-hoonigan", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Why are so many car YouTubers quitting?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T11:49:03+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Disney Plus logo on a beige and purple background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/M2bgnZvPuK2bFbVrLByh--qXNuo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506524/acastro_STK080_disneyPlus_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"M4Mqw5\">Disney\u2019s streaming business has finally become profitable. In <a href=\"https://thewaltdisneycompany.com/app/uploads/2024/08/q3-fy24-earnings.pdf\">its Q3 earnings results released on Wednesday</a>, the company reported making $47 million off Disney Plus, Hulu, and ESPN Plus.</p>\n<p id=\"JB5zYX\">Like other streamers, Disney has struggled with making its streaming business profitable. At the same time last year, Disney Plus, ESPN Plus, and Hulu recorded a $512 million loss. Things started to turn around last quarter when both <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/7/24150986/disney-streaming-business-earnings-q2-2024\">Disney Plu", "id": 990144, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214898/disney-streaming-business-profitable-earnings-q3-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Disney\u2019s streaming business turned a profit for the first time", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T10:19:47+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Ryzen 9 9950X CPU\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/G6NKiTOurFHEdGmBoAgUV7e4waU=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506446/Ryzen_9000_7.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: AMD</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"O77vW0\">AMD has finally <a href=\"https://x.com/AMDRyzen/status/1820956835794358451\">revealed</a> the launch prices for its new range of Ryzen 9000 desktop CPUs, and it\u2019s pricing them slightly lower than the Ryzen 7000 launch prices. The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/2/24168544/amd-zen-5-ryzen-9-9950x-cpu-computex-2024\">flagship Ryzen 9 9950X</a> with 16 cores will be priced at $649, which is $50 less than the $699 Ryzen 9 7950X that launched nearly two years ago. The rest of the lineup are priced between $20 and $50 less than equivalent Ryzen 7000 CPUs.</p>\n<p id=\"StCf4r\">After a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/24/24205416/amd-zen-5-ryzen-9000-desktop-delay\">delay to the launch</a> of its", "id": 989747, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215164/amd-ryzen-9000-series-pricing-launch-dates", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AMD\u2019s new Ryzen 9000 CPUs are cheaper than its previous-gen chips", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-07T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Ford Mustang e-bike\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YXnKRSoNnTsy3RKUWSdXz7TvyJQ=/0x243:7680x5363/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73506442/FORD_MUSTANG__HERITAGE.631.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Ford</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SAKqjG\">Ford announced today that it would be working with bike company N plus to introduce two new e-bikes inspired by the automaker\u2019s most iconic brands, the Bronco and Mustang. </p>\n<p id=\"zrhExw\">There\u2019s nothing new about <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/10/25/23422664/rivian-ebike-cars-electric-motors-porsche-bosch\">car companies working with bike manufacturers to co-develop e-bikes</a> in the hopes of exciting gear heads. GM, Porsche, Jeep, Polestar, and others have tried to do the same, with varying degrees of success. But Ford says its bikes will be unique insofar as they are directly tied to two of the company\u2019s most storied models. </p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><asi", "id": 989370, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214731/ford-ebike-bronco-mustang-specs-price-photos", 